The hive metastore legacy catalog.

Every workspace that pre-dates unity catalog still has a special catalog called hive metastore. It's the workspace-local metastore — tables created with the legacy two-part name, schema dot table, live there.

There are two facts to lock in. First, hive metastore is per-workspace, not regional. Two workspaces have two completely independent hive metastore catalogs, which means there's no cross-workspace governance.

Second, new tables should never land in hive metastore. Treat it strictly as legacy. You migrate its contents into a real unity catalog catalog using the upgrade tooling or the sync-table command.

So whenever the exam contrasts a hive-metastore-dot-default name against a proper three-part unity catalog name, the three-part name is always the right pattern.
